				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$Adp_i^{get}$$\end{document} we use probit regressions, which apply the maximum likelihood principle to cumulative normal distributions. The coefficients tell the impact of the independent variables on the respective response probabilities. Analogously, we apply an ordered probit regression to fit Adpiobj\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
